

###Block: Racial / General Feats
# Able Learner - cannot implement today
Able Learner		SOURCEPAGE:p.150	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial.FirstLevel	PREVARLT:FirstLevelFeatTaken,FirstLevelFeatAllowed	DESC:You have a great aptitude for learning.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Human or doppelganger.	BENEFIT:All skill ranks cost 1 skill point for you to purchase, even if the skill is cross-class for you. The maximum number of ranks you can purchase in a cross-class skill remains the same. This feat does not affect the skill point cost to learn a language or to gain literacy (for a barbarian or other illiterate character). Normal: Cross-class skills cost 2 skill points per rank. Special: This feat may only be taken at 1st level.
Bright Sigil		SOURCEPAGE:p.150	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You have established a greater degree of control over your sigils. When you concentrate, you can emit strong illumination from the glowing symbols that surround your head.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Illumian.	BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can increase the illumination from your illumian sigils to provide a bright glow. Your sigils shed illumination equivalent to a daylight spell. The brighter light lasts as long as you concentrate, and for 1 round thereafter. Normal: An illumian's sigils ordinarily emit a 5-foot radius of shadowy illumination, equivalent to a candle.
Channeled Rage		SOURCEPAGE:p.150	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You can focus your rage to counter charms and compulsions.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Half-orc, ability to rage.	PRERACE:1,Half-Orc	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Rage	BENEFIT:You may spend one of your daily uses of rage as an immediate action to add your Strength bonus on a Will saving throw.
City Slicker		SOURCEPAGE:p.150	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.FirstLevel	PREVARLT:FirstLevelFeatTaken,FirstLevelFeatAllowed	DESC:You are very familiar with city life and the inner workings of your hometown.	BENEFIT:Disguise, Forgery, Gather Information, and Knowledge (local) are always class skills for you. Special: This feat may only be taken at 1st level.	CSKILL:Disguise|Forgery|Gather Information|Knowledge (Local)
Complementary Insight	SOURCEPAGE:p.150	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You get more out of having skills that work well together.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Half-elf.	PRERACE:1,Half-Elf	BENEFIT:Having 5 or more ranks in a skill gives you a +3 bonus on skill checks with each of its synergistic skills, as noted in the skill description. Normal: Synergistic skills provide a +2 bonus on skill checks.	BONUS:VAR|SynergyBonus|1
Diverse Background	SOURCEPAGE:p.150	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial.FirstLevel	PREVARLT:FirstLevelFeatTaken,FirstLevelFeatAllowed	DESC:You have a wide and diverse background, giving you a greater understanding of different occupations.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Half-human.	BENEFIT:Choose one class. That class is also a favored class for you. Special: This feat may only be taken at 1st level.	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Favored_Class|1	DEFINE:POOL_Favored_Class|0
Enhanced Power Sigils	SOURCEPAGE:p.152	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:Your illumian power sigils are more powerful than normal.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Illumian, two power sigils.	PRERACE:1,Illumian	PREVARGTEQ:Power_Sigil_Count,2	BENEFIT:The bonuses granted by each of your power sigils improve by 1. Normal: Without this feat, the bonuses granted by each of your power sigils are equal to the number of power sigils you possess.	BONUS:VAR|Power_Sigil_Bonus|1
Fearless Destiny		SOURCEPAGE:p.152	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:Your grand destiny allows you to avoid death.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Human or half-human, Heroic Destiny, character level 6th.	PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Human	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Heroic Destiny	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=6	BENEFIT:Once per day, any effect that would reduce you to -10 hit points or fewer instead reduces you to -9 hit points and leaves you in a stable condition. Effects that kill you without reducing you to -10 hit points (such as death effects or disintegrate) function normally.
Heroic Destiny		SOURCEPAGE:p.152	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You have a destiny to fulfill.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Human or half-human.	PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Human	BENEFIT:Once per day, before you make an attack roll, ability check, skill check, saving throw, or caster level check, you may roll 1d6 and add it as a bonus on the roll, check, or save.
Human Heritage		SOURCEPAGE:p.152	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial.FirstLevel	PREVARLT:FirstLevelFeatTaken,FirstLevelFeatAllowed	DESC:Your human heritage is more prominent than in others of your kind.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Half-human race or human-descended race.	PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Human	!PRERACE:1,Human	BENEFIT:You are treated as a humanoid with the human subtype for the purpose of adjudicating all effects. If you are not a humanoid, your type changes to humanoid and you gain the human subtype. If you are already a humanoid, you gain the human subtype. In either case, you retain any other subtypes you had (such as orc or extraplanar), and you retain any traits common to all creatures of your original type (such as darkvision). You gain 4 additional skill points. Special: This feat may only be taken at 1st level. See the Variant: Half-Humans and Humanlike Races sidebar, page 150, for more about races eligible to select this feat.	TEMPLATE:Assign Race Type ~ Humanoid|Assign Subtype ~ Human
Improved Sigil (Aesh)	SOURCEPAGE:p.152	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You tap into your aesh power sigil to gain enhanced accuracy with your favored melee weapons.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Illumian, aesh power sigil.	PRERACE:1,Illumian	BENEFIT:Your aesh power sigil grants you a +1 insight bonus per power sigil on melee weapon damage rolls with any weapon with which you have selected the Weapon Focus feat.
Improved Sigil (Hoon)	SOURCEPAGE:p.152	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You tap into your hoon power sigil to help survive deadly conditions.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Illumian, hoon power sigil.	PRERACE:1,Illumian	BENEFIT:Your hoon power sigil grants you a +1 insight bonus per power sigil on saving throws against death effects, on saves to avoid death by massive damage, and on Fortitude saves to avoid nonlethal damage from hot and cold environments or to resist damage from suffocation.
Improved Sigil (Krau)	SOURCEPAGE:p.153	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You tap into your krau power sigil to augment the energy of your magical utterances.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Illumian, krau power sigil.	PRERACE:1,Illumian	BENEFIT:Choose a number of spells with verbal components that you can cast equal to the number of power sigils you have. When you cast one of the chosen spells, the spell's effective level is increased by 1 (as if affected by the Heighten Spell feat, but with no change to the spell's casting time or spell slot). All effects dependent on spell level are calculated according to the heightened level. Whenever you gain the ability to cast a new level of spells, you can reassign the spells you've chosen to be enhanced by this feat. For example, a wizard who reaches 3rd level and gains the ability to cast 2nd-level spells may reassign the spells affected by this feat. Special: If you cast one of your chosen spells using the Silent Spell feat, this feat has no effect.
Improved Sigil (Naen)	SOURCEPAGE:p.153	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You tap into your naen power sigil to see through illusions and resist language-based effects.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Illumian, naen power sigil.	PRERACE:1,Illumian	BENEFIT:Your naen power sigil grants you a +1 insight bonus per power sigil on saving throws against illusions and against language-dependent effects.
Improved Sigil (Uur)	SOURCEPAGE:p.153	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You tap into your uur power sigil to gain enhanced accuracy with ranged weapons.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Illumian, uur power sigil.	PRERACE:1,Illumian	BENEFIT:Your uur power sigil grants you a +1 insight bonus per power sigil on ranged weapon damage rolls whenever your target is denied its Dexterity bonus to Armor Class.
Improved Sigil (Vaul)	SOURCEPAGE:p.153	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You tap into your vaul power sigil to resist mental effects.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Illumian, vaul power sigil.	PRERACE:1,Illumian	BENEFIT:Your vaul power sigil grants you a +1 insight bonus per power sigil on saving throws against mind-affecting spells and abilities.
Inside Connection		SOURCEPAGE:p.153	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	DESC:Choose a specific organization, such as a town's militia, a particular church, a guild, or one of the illumian cabals (see Chapter 3). You have strong personal connections within that organization, as well as insight into its membership.	BENEFIT:You gain a +4 circumstance bonus on Bluff, Diplomacy, Gather Information, Knowledge (local), and Sense Motive checks made in conjunction with that organization. Special: You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take this feat, it applies to a new organization. The DM should limit characters to selecting only those organizations with which they have a positive or neutral relationship. For instance, a character might not be allowed to select an enemy organization, or one whose existence and/or operations aren't well known to him.
Menacing Demeanor		SOURCEPAGE:p.153	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You can tap into your savage heritage to improve your intimidation techniques.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Orc blood or orc subtype.	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Orc Blood,Orc ~ Orc Blood],[PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Orc]	BENEFIT:You gain a +4 bonus on Intimidate checks.	BONUS:SKILL|Intimidate|4
Protected Destiny		SOURCEPAGE:p.153	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:Your heroic destiny is guarded against the whims of misfortune.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Human or half-human, Heroic Destiny, character level 3rd.	PRERACE:1,RACESUBTYPE=Human	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Heroic Destiny	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=3	BENEFIT:Once per day, if you roll a natural 1 on a saving throw, you may reroll the save.
Resourceful Buyer		SOURCEPAGE:p.153	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	DESC:You know where to look in a community for anything you need.	BENEFIT:Whenever you are buying goods, the community you're in is treated as one category larger for the purpose of determining the community's gold piece limit on the most expensive item available (see Table 5-2: Random Town Generation, page 137 of the Dungeon Master's Guide). For example, when you are in a village, the gold piece limit on the most expensive item available to you is 800 gp rather than 200 gp. Special: This benefit doesn't stack with any other effect that grants a similar benefit.
Smatterings			SOURCEPAGE:p.153	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	DESC:You have a talent for acquiring languages-at least enough of each one to get by.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Int 13.	PRESTAT:1,INT=13	BENEFIT:You can learn enough of a language to ask and understand simple questions, explanations, and instructions. This benefit only applies to verbal communication. After 2d6 days of listening to a new language, you know enough to ask simple questions and to follow simple directions. Upon every future encounter with this language, you need only 1d4 days to regain that knowledge.
Sociable Personality	SOURCEPAGE:p.153	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You are adroit at avoiding social gaffes.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Half-elf, Cha 13.	PRERACE:1,Half-Elf	PRESTAT:1,CHA=13	BENEFIT:You may reroll any Diplomacy or Gather Information checks. You must take the result of the reroll, even if it's worse than the original roll.
Subtle Sigil		SOURCEPAGE:p.154	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Racial	DESC:You are able to fade your sigils into invisibility, but still tap their magical energy.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Illumian.	PRERACE:1,Illumian	BENEFIT:You can make your sigils disappear or reappear as a free action. You gain the full benefits of your power sigils even when they are not visible. Normal: Illumians can douse their sigils or make them reappear with a standard action, and they lose the benefits of their power sigils as long as they are doused.
Urban Stealth		SOURCEPAGE:p.154	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	DESC:You are particularly adept at moving quietly and unnoticed through the city.	PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Knowledge (local) 2 ranks.	PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (local)=2	BENEFIT:You gain a +3 bonus on Hide and Move Silently checks in a small city or larger community. This bonus applies only when you are outside-trying to hide in a bedroom or office does not benefit from this feat, since your knowledge of urban environments is no help in such confined spaces.
Urban Tracking		SOURCEPAGE:p.154	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General	DESC:You can track down the location of missing persons or wanted individuals within communities.	BENEFIT:To find the trail of an individual or to follow it for 1 hour requires a Gather Information check. You must make another Gather Information check for every hour of the search, as well as each time the trail becomes difficult to follow, such as when it moves to a different area of town. The DC of the check, and the number of checks required to track down your quarry, depend on the community size and the conditions; see the table below. If you fail a Gather Information check, you can retry after 1 hour of questioning. The DM should roll the number of checks required secretly, so that the player doesn't know exactly how long the task will require. Normal: A character without this feat can use Gather Information to find out information about a particular individual, but each check takes 1d4+1 hours and doesn't allow effective trailing. Special: You can cut the time per Gather Information check in half (to 30 minutes per check), but you take a -5 penalty on the check.

