Arcane Insight	SOURCEPAGE:p.154	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Initiate	DESC:By immersing yourself in the teachings of Boccob, you have unearthed magical secrets and gained special insight into arcane spellcasting.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cleric level 3rd, deity Boccob.	PRECLASS:1,Cleric=3	PREDEITY:1,Boccob	BENEFIT:Add Knowledge (arcana) to your list of cleric class skills. You gain a +2 insight bonus on Spellcraft checks. In addition, you may add the following spells to your cleric spell list:	BENEFIT:&nl;1st True Strike: +20 on your next attack roll.	BENEFIT:&nl;3rd Arcane Sight: Magical auras become visible to you.	BENEFIT:&nl;5th Rary's Telepathic Bond: Link lets allies communicate.	BENEFIT:&nl;7th Arcane Sight, Greater: As arcane sight, but also reveals magic effects on creatures and objects.	BENEFIT:&nl;8th Moment of Prescience: You gain insight bonus on a single attack roll, check, or save.	BONUS:SKILL|Spellcraft|2|TYPE=Insight	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=1|True Strike	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=3|Arcane Sight	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=5|Telepathic Bond	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=7|Arcane Sight (Greater)	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=8|Moment of Prescience
Dread Tyranny	SOURCEPAGE:p.154	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Initiate	DESC:A devoted student of Hextor's militant teachings, you are skilled at intimidating and dominating weaker beings.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cleric level 3rd, Str 13, deity Hextor.	PRECLASS:1,Cleric=3	PREDEITY:1,Hextor	PRESTAT:1,STR=13	BENEFIT:Add Intimidate to your list of cleric class skills. You add your Strength bonus in addition to your Charisma bonus on Intimidate checks. Furthermore, when you use a lethal weapon to deal nonlethal damage, you lessen the penalty on attack rolls by 2 (-2 penalty instead of -4). In addition, you may add the following spells to your cleric spell list:	BENEFIT:&nl;2nd Scare: Frightens creatures of less than 6 HD.	BENEFIT:&nl;4th Evard's Black Tentacles: Tentacles grapple all within 15-ft. spread.	BENEFIT:&nl;5th Dominate Person: Controls humanoid telepathically.	BENEFIT:&nl;6th Eyebite: Target becomes panicked, sickened, and comatose.	BENEFIT:&nl;8th Demand: Delivers short message and suggestion anywhere, instantly.	BENEFIT:&nl;9th Dominate Monster: As dominate person, but any creature.	BONUS:SKILL|Intimidate|STR	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=2|Scare	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=4|Black Tentacles	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=5|Dominate Person	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=6|Eyebite	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=8|Demand	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=9|Dominate Monster
Eternal Strength	SOURCEPAGE:p.155	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Initiate	DESC:You have taken Kord's fighting ways to heart. Throwing yourself into every brawl, you draw upon your mighty deity's strength.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cleric level 5th, Str 13, deity Kord.	PRECLASS:1,Cleric=3	PREDEITY:1,Kord	PRESTAT:1,STR=13	BENEFIT:You gain a +4 bonus on saving throws to resist effects that deal Strength damage or cause Strength drain. In addition, you may add the following spells to your cleric spell list:	BENEFIT:&nl;3rd Heroism: Gives +2 bonus on attack rolls, saves, and skill checks.	BENEFIT:&nl;5th Waves of Fatigue: Several targets become fatigued.	BENEFIT:&nl;6th Heroism, Greater: Gives +4 bonus on attack rolls, saves, skill checks; immunity to fear; temporary hp.	BENEFIT:&nl;7th Waves of Exhaustion: Several targets become exhausted.	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=3|Heroism	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=5|Waves of Fatigue	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=6|Heroism (Greater)	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=7|Waves of Exhaustion
Far Horizons	SOURCEPAGE:p.155	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Initiate	DESC:By dedicating yourself to the philosophies of Fharlanghn, you have become a more world-wise and capable traveler.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cleric level 1st, deity Fharlanghn.	PRECLASS:1,Cleric=1	PREDEITY:1,Fharlanghn	BENEFIT:Add Climb, Jump, and Swim to your list of cleric class skills. Furthermore, you always know the direction of north from your current position. You cannot use this extraordinary ability in any environment where "north" does not exist. In addition, you may add the following spells to your cleric spell list:	BENEFIT:&nl;1st Expeditious Retreat: Your speed increases by 30 ft.	BENEFIT:&nl;3rd Leomund's Tiny Hut: Creates shelter for ten creatures.	BENEFIT:&nl;5th Overland Flight: You fly at a speed of 40 ft. and can hustle over long distances.	BENEFIT:&nl;6th Shadow Walk: Step into shadow to travel rapidly.	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=1|Expeditious Retreat	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=3|Tiny Hut	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=5|Overland Flight	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=6|Shadow Walk
Law Inviolate	SOURCEPAGE:p.155	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Initiate	DESC:Your unshakable faith in St. Cuthbert allows you to better apprehend fugitives or overcome villains who transgress the law.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cleric level 1st, must be lawful, deity St. Cuthbert.	PRECLASS:1,Cleric=1	PREDEITY:1,St. Cuthbert	PREALIGN:LG,LN,LE	BENEFIT:Your natural weapons, as well as any weapons you wield, are treated as lawful-aligned for the purpose of overcoming damage reduction. In addition, you may add the following spells to your cleric spell list:	BENEFIT:&nl;1st Color Spray: Knocks unconscious, blinds, and/or stuns 1d6 weak creatures.	BENEFIT:&nl;2nd Daze Monster: Living creature of 6 HD or less loses next action.	BENEFIT:&nl;3rd Suggestion: Compels subject to follow stated course of action.	BENEFIT:&nl;5th Passwall: Creates passage through wood or stone wall.	BENEFIT:&nl;6th Suggestion, Mass: As suggestion, plus one subject/ level.	BENEFIT:&nl;8th Power Word Stun: Stuns creature with 150 hp or less.	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=1|Color Spray	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=2|Daze Monster	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=3|Passwall	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=5|Suggestion (Mass)	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=8|Power Word Stun
Radiant Fire	SOURCEPAGE:p.155	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Initiate	DESC:Pelor has ignited your faith and conviction, making you better able to fight the creatures of darkness.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cleric level 3rd, deity Pelor.	PRECLASS:1,Cleric=3	PREDEITY:1,Pelor	BENEFIT:You gain a +2 insight bonus on damage rolls against creatures with the evil subtype. In addition, you may add the following spells to your cleric spell list:	BENEFIT:&nl;2nd Scorching Ray: Ranged touch attack deals 4d6 fire damage, +1 ray/four levels (maximum 3).	BENEFIT:&nl;3rd Summon Monster III*: Calls extraplanar creature to fight for you.	BENEFIT:&nl;5th Summon Monster V*: Calls extraplanar creature to fight for you.	BENEFIT:&nl;6th Summon Monster VI*: Calls extraplanar creature to fight for you.	BENEFIT:&nl;8th Summon Monster VIII*: Calls extraplanar creature to fight for you.	BENEFIT:&nl;*Fire elementals only.	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=2|Scorching Ray	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=4|Summon Monster III (Fire elementals only)	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=5|Summon Monster V (Fire elementals only)	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=6|Summon Monster VI (Fire elementals only)	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=8|Summon Monster VIII (Fire elementals only)	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=9|Dominate Monster
Undying Fate	SOURCEPAGE:p.155	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Initiate	DESC:You have pledged your unswerving obedience to Wee Jas, and she in turn has granted you special insight into life and death.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cleric level 3rd, deity Wee Jas.	PRECLASS:1,Cleric=3	PREDEITY:1,Wee Jas	BENEFIT:As a swift action, you can determine how close creatures are to death. This extraordinary ability can be used at will but otherwise functions like the deathwatch spell. In addition, you may add the following spells to your cleric spell list:	BENEFIT:&nl;2nd False Life: Gain 1d10 temporary hp +1/level (max +10).	BENEFIT:&nl;3rd Halt Undead: Immobilizes undead for 1 round/level.	BENEFIT:&nl;5th Blight: Withers one plant or deals 1d6/level damage to plant creature.	BENEFIT:&nl;7th Finger of Death: Kills one subject or deals 3d6 damage +1/level (max +25).	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=2|False Life	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=3|Halt Undead	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=5|Blight	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=7|Finger of Death
Whispered Secrets	SOURCEPAGE:p.155	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Initiate	DESC:You revere the Maimed Lord and have devoted your miserable, worthless life to learning but a few of the Whispered One's secrets.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Cleric level 1st, deity Vecna.	PRECLASS:1,Cleric=1	PREDEITY:1,Vecna	BENEFIT:Add Listen and Spot to your list of cleric class skills. Furthermore, you automatically become aware of any attempt to observe you by means of a divination (scrying) spell or effect. This extraordinary ability does not enable you to discern the scrier, the type of scrying device or spell used, or the scrier's location. In addition, you may add the following spells to your cleric spell list:	BENEFIT:&nl;1st Disguise Self: Changes your appearance.	BENEFIT:&nl;2nd Darkvision: See 60 ft. in total darkness.	BENEFIT:&nl;3rd Glibness: You gain +30 on Bluff checks and your lies can escape magical discernment.	BENEFIT:&nl;4th Arcane Eye: Invisible floating eye moves 30 ft./round.	BENEFIT:&nl;5th Prying Eyes: 1d4 +1/level floating eyes scout for you.	BENEFIT:&nl;6th Analyze DweomerF: Reveals magical aspects of subject.	BENEFIT:&nl;8th Mind Blank: Subject is immune to mental/emotional magic and scrying.	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=1|Disguise Self	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=2|Darkvision	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=3|Glibness	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=4|Arcane Eye	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=5|Prying Eyes	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=6|Analyze Dweomer	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=8|Mind Blank

###Block: Tactical Feats
Crowd Tactics	SOURCEPAGE:p.156	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Tactical	DESC:You are adept at moving through and fighting in crowds.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Hide 5 ranks, Dodge.	PRESKILL:1,Hide=5	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dodge	BENEFIT:The Crowd Tactics feat enables the use of three tactical maneuvers. You only gain these benefits if the crowd is indifferent or friendly.	BENEFIT:&nl;Moving with the Flow: Entering a square with a crowd in it does not cost you extra movement.	BENEFIT:&nl;One with the Crowd: You gain a +4 bonus on Hide checks made in square with a crowd.	BENEFIT:&nl;Master of the Mob: You gain a +4 bonus on Diplomacy or Intimidate checks when attempting to direct a crowd.	BENEFIT:&nl;Normal: See page 100 of the Dungeon Master's Guide for rules on crowds.
Roofwalker		SOURCEPAGE:p.156	CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Tactical	DESC:You are adept at moving and fighting on rooftops and ledges.	PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Balance 5 ranks, Jump 5 ranks, Dodge, Mobility.	PRESKILL:2,Balance=5,Jump=5	PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dodge,Mobility	BENEFIT:The Roofwalker feat enables the use of three tactical maneuvers.	BENEFIT:&nl;Fleet of Feet: You can walk across a precarious surface more quickly than normal. You can move at your full speed without taking a -5 penalty on your Balance check.	BENEFIT:&nl;Graceful Drop: If you intentionally jump from a height, you take less damage than you would if you fell. If you succeed on a Jump check when jumping down (see page 77 of the Player's Handbook), you take falling damage as if you had dropped 20 fewer feet than you actually did.	BENEFIT:&nl;Master of the Roof: You know how to use the slopes to your advantage. You gain a +1 dodge bonus to AC against any opponent who is at a different elevation from you.
